>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/02 10:31:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4498.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ashley-design.com/byrnes/head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Haste ...</span><hr size=1> Does haste make or break a tank?<br>
<br>
I have been playing this game for way to long but for the most part I dont buy into stats on stuff~.  There are thousands of warriors out there.  They all want 1200AC and 5000+ HP.  If you buy/get X, Y, and Z you can look like every other tank out there, and tank A can be out taunted by tank B.  I have grouped with DE warriors and Troll warriors as well as Paladins.  Everyone is either good or bad and I dont think it depends on their class, their weaps, or for the most part their equipment.  The above is very generic and based on &quot;my beliefs&quot; which means its full of holes<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
I do think that ONE major difference is the base haste on the tank.  I want to know is a RBB worth 45K or a CoF 100K ... will these make a 50% difference between ie. someone with a RBB and a fbss.  My tank is pretty phat with one thing missing .. a good haste item.<br>
<br>
I have grouped with many tanks over then years and have been amazed at how well they do there thing.  My tank has never been able to get over that &quot;wow&quot; hurdle and the only reason I can think of is the haste.<br>
<br>
Please let me know what ya think ... besides that I am stupid troll cleric.<br>
<br>
(BTW I'm not talking about end game tanks ... 50-60 types with only a few AA or pre-Velious) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">[61 High Priest] <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51690">Dasgood Dasbad (Sexy Dwarf) - ToT - Bristlebane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ashley-design.com/byrnes/dread.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thorilan>thorilan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 296<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/02 7:00:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4498.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Haste ...</span><hr size=1> well as i see it .<br>
<br>
people want this equipment for a reason . to better do thier job . so naturaly they will all look similar.<br>
<br>
but you are correct player skill has a factor in there to.<br>
the thing about haste is it basically is a damage doing item and that only effects 2 parts of your job ( agro and damge)<br>
<br>
for agro it means hitting more so more possible procs in same amount of time along with the extra damage. <br>
<br>
it is for most the second priority ( first being serviving due to good equipment with ac hp  resists ect ect ect ) <br>
and for others its first priority ( doing damage  to get the mob dead faster ect ect ect) <br>
<br>
where you put it personaly depends on your play style <br>
<br>
i love haste and notice a big diference from a cof and rbg so i put the priority a bit high. <br>
( granted i have great gear already for my lvl)<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91310">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...?num=91310</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyrdlan>Wyrdlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/02 10:11:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4498.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eq-viatores.org/book.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Haste ...</span><hr size=1> Depends on who you group with and what you are swinging.<br>
<br>
Windblade for me is 46/44 unhasted (level 51).  It does a VERY nice job.  I wear an SoDB. (46 / 35)  If I had an RBB (46 / 33 ) I might notice a difference if I was all on my own, but I doubt it.<br>
<br>
But I'm not on my own.<br>
<br>
With SLTW it becomes a question of 84% haste (46/24) against 91% haste (46/23).  My thought is you could parse it a dozen times and sometimes one would win and sometimes the other would.<br>
<br>
I'm willing to bet &quot;Haunting Visage&quot; would play a much larger roll in controlling agro than the difference in belts at that point, even though I'd pick up some nice stats with the RBB.<br>
<br>
I imagine the largest difference once you have 'good' gear ( 1200 AC/4kHP) won't be in exact haste percentage, it's in knowing where to stand and which of your friends to trust the most. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub38.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm38.showMessage?topicID=409.topic"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.eq-viatores.org/sig.php"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=terailgrimtooth>Terail Grimtooth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/02 12:39:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4498.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Haste ...</span><hr size=1> Haste to me is like Clarity (1,2,3 or 4) for a caster,  higher haste makes me better at what i do so the higher the haste is the more rounds i will do so look at it that way i guess, haste is a nice toy for us warriors that have the cash to play around with oh and allso the wepons....allways the wepons. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
-my 2cp <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.soliath.com/signatures/terail.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
44 TROLL WARRIOR<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=243427"> MY GEAR</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Proud Member of <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;">DA SKURGE!!</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gedes>Gedes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/02 9:29:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4498.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Haste ...</span><hr size=1> I've got to tell you that I have never been a large fan of haste.  All my lower levels I looked at haste as a way for warriors to try to do more damage for pure eye candy.  I believed that we were here to take damage, not deal it. <br>
<br>
 It didn't really occur to me until just recently that I can have all the AC and hit points in the world, but if the mob won't hit me, they don't matter.  So, I ditched my Ancient Seahorse Hide cloak (20ac 25hit points) and picked up a Siblisan Beserker Cloak.  The difference in aggro was night and day.  I went from struggling to hold aggro from monks and rogues to being able to position mobs as I wanted them without the mob turning and whacking anything else around it.  <br>
<br>
Is there a huge difference between items?  Well, 27% on my cloak is huge compared to no haste before.  If each hit produces aggro, then 36% haste (or 41% in a more rare case) would produce 9% more aggro than what I currently have. <br>
<br>
Did that help?  Or even answer the original question? lol <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2372"> Thor Lost Myrmidon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/c_warrior.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;It's never too late to be what you might have been - George Eliot&quot;<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=1ludor>1Ludor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/02 11:54:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4498.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Haste ...</span><hr size=1> 1. get the best weapons u can. windblade, dismay axe, or something similiar is probably best depending on your budget. xp groups are all about dmg, especially prepop. Hp gear is more important in pop where mobs really hit.<br>
<br>
2. cof is over rated, get an rbb and heirophant cloak instead. u will max haste with sos, wr, or even aq.<br>
<br>
3. get all the deity armor u can find if you got that option. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cslochraven>CSLochraven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 277<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/02 8:15:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4498.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gs.cdnow.com/graphics/COVERART/local/L/80/01/00138001.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Haste ...</span><hr size=1> The original poster isn't uber, and probably doesn't always get groups with top notch enchanters.  And what if he wanted to solo?  <br>
<br>
I have a CoF and I love it.  With decent resources you can get better HP combinations with CoF than an RBB.<br>
<br>
Really your own preference though. <p>&lt;b&gt;Lochraven&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;<br>
